lic <b>Ó Beargha</b> ‘descendant of <i>Beargh</i>’, a byname meaning ‘plunderer’.","Irish and Manx: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Báire</b> ‘descendant of <i>Báire</i>’, a short form of either of two Gaelic personal names, <i>Bairrfhionn</i> or <i>Fionnbharr</i>, both meaning ‘fair-topped’. This may also be the source of the Manx name <i>Barry</i>, whose family's main seat was Ballavarry in Kirk Andreas."]},{"name":"Bery","meanings":["English: variant of   Berry  .","Hungarian (<b>Béry</b>): habitational name for someone from any of various places called Bér, in Baranya, Komárom, Nógrád, Pest, Vas, or Zala counties."]},{"name":"Beery","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of <b>Ó Béara</b>. See   Berry   and   O'Berry  .","Americanized form of Swiss German   Bieri  ."]},{"name":"Berrie","meanings":["Scottish:","(Glasgow): from Middle English or Older Scots <i>(atte) beri</i> ‘(at the) manor house’, see   Berry  .","variant   Barrie  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":40,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":113,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Berry was born in 1342, in Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England, his father, Osmond Barry, was 27 and his mother, Alice Mikelfelde, was 102. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Wachesham."},"et":{"1342–":"1342–Surnud","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1347–1402":"1347–1402","1369–1433":"1369–1433","1315–Male":"1315–Surnud","1240–Female":"1240–Surnud","1315":"1315","1369":"1369","1402":"1402","1347":"1347","1455":"1455","1433":"1433","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1382":"1382","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, England","Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England":"Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1342–":"1342–Kuollut","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1347–1402":"1347–1402","1369–1433":"1369–1433","1315–Male":"1315–Kuollut","1240–Female":"1240–Kuollut","1315":"1315","1369":"1369","1402":"1402","1347":"1347","1455":"1455","1433":"1433","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1382":"1382","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, England","Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England":"Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1342–":"1342–Décédé","1342–Male":"1342–Décédé","1347–1402":"1347–1402","1369–1433":"1369–1433","1315–Male":"1315–Décédé","1240–Female":"1240–Décédée","1315":"1315","1369":"1369","1402":"1402","1347":"1347","1455":"1455","1433":"1433","1342":"1342","1340":"1340","1240":"1240","1382":"1382","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, Angleterre","Kelshall, Hertfordshire, England":"Kelshall, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John Berry est né en 1342, à Kelshall, Hertfordshire, Angleterre, son père, Osmond Barry, avait 27 ans et sa mère, Alice Mikelfelde, avait 102 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Elizabeth Wachesham."},"de":{"1342–":"1342–Verstorben","1342–Male":"1342–Verstorben","1347–1402":"1347–1402","1369–1433":"1369–1433","1315–Male":"1315–Verstor